    "en": "Descended from white German Spitz dogs brought to America by German immigrants. Name changed from German Spitz to American Eskimo Dog during World War I due to anti-German sentiment. Became popular circus performers in the 19th and early 20th centuries, recognized by AKC in 1994",
    "zh": "源自德国移民带到美国的白色德国狐狸犬。第一次世界大战期间因反德情绪，名称从德国狐狸犬改为美国爱斯基摩犬。19世纪至20世纪初成为受欢迎的马戏团表演犬，1994年获美国养犬俱乐部认可。"
